Fill a large #saucepan{} with water and bring to the boil. Chop the @potatoes{700} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). When boiling, pop the potatoes into the pan and cook until just tender, ~{10-12%minutes}. TIP: The potato is cooked when you can easily slip a knife through. Once done, drain in a #colander{} and set to one side. Keep the pan! Preheat your #grill{} to high.

Meanwhile, trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}. Halve lengthways then thinly slice widthways. Quarter the @closed cup mushrooms{150}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated). Heat a splash of @olive oil in a #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. Once hot, add the mushrooms and stir-fry until starting to brown, ~{5-6%minutes}. Add the leek, cook for ~{2%minutes}, then add the @sliced spring greens{150}(sliced) and garlic to the pan. Cook until wilted, ~{2-3%minutes}, stirring regularly.

Once the greens have wilted, stir the @plain flour{8}(stirred continuously) into the pan. Stirring continuously, cook for ~{1%minute} then pour in the @water{100}, @creme fraiche{150}, @KNORR chicken stock{1} and half the @dijon mustard{1}. Stir until everything is well combined, slowly bring to the boil, then remove the pan from the heat. Keep 100g of @ham hock{200} for your lunch and gently mix the rest into the creamy sauce. Season to taste with a good pinch of @salt and @ground black pepper. Preheat your grill to high.

Refill the saucepan with water and bring to the boil. Meanwhile, transfer the filling into a small #ovenproof dish{}. Leaving two small portions of potato to the side, distribute the rest of the potato on top of the creamy filling. Sprinkle the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40} all over, then pop under the grill until golden and bubbling, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Halve the @tenderstem® broccoli{80}(halved widthways). Once the water is boiling, add it to the pan and cook until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice the @spring onions{2}(trimmed and sliced) and zest and halve the @lemon{1}. When the broccoli is done, drain in the colander and quickly run under cold water until cool. Set to one side, this is for your lunch! Time to eat. Once the gratin is ready, divide between your #bowls{}. Dig in!

To finish the salad, pop the broccoli, @pea shoots{40}, spring onions, reserved potatoes and ham hock into a #bowl{}. Gently toss together, then transfer to suitable #containers{}. Mix the remaining mustard, a squeeze of lemon juice, a pinch of lemon zest and the @olive oil together and pour into small containers. Refrigerate overnight. Dress the salad when ready to eat. Enjoy!